Describe an occassion when you waited a long time for a nice thing.
- when it happened
- what the nice thing was
- how long you waited
- why you waited for a long time
- explain how you felt about the experience

I’d like to talk about a time when I had to wait quite a long time for something meaningful, which was the end of the COVID-19 pandemic and a return to normal life.

This happened around two years ago, during the second wave of the pandemic in Vietnam. At that time, strict social distancing measures were in place, and people were required to stay at home unless it was absolutely necessary to go out. Everyday activities were heavily restricted, and there was a constant sense of uncertainty and concern about the situation.

For me, the “nice thing” I was waiting for was simply the chance to go back to my normal routine, such as attending classes in person and meeting up with friends. However, I had to wait for nearly six months before things gradually improved and restrictions were lifted.

The reason it took so long was that vaccination rates were still low at the time, and the government needed to take strict measures to control the spread of the virus. During that period, I had to adapt to online learning and spent most of my time at home. Although I tried to keep myself entertained by watching movies or series, it sometimes felt quite isolating.

When the situation finally got better and life began to return to normal, I felt an overwhelming sense of relief and happiness. It was such a simple thing, but after waiting for so long, it became incredibly meaningful.

Looking back, that experience taught me to appreciate the small things in life and not take everyday freedoms for granted.
